summary: Do you guys know what I like the most about the commentary crew? That they actually interact with their viewers! Like, I just...
body:
Do you guys know what I like the most about the commentary crew? That they actually interact with their viewers! Like, I just watched Hooverr’s instagram live and he read like at least half of my comments and responded to them?? And Ani, Kappa, Aksel, Quackity AND Henry all commented on the same video I made where they were mentioned???

Like, most youtubers don’t do this but these people do and it honestly makes me so happy!

title: Amity fest gone wrong
body:
Prompt - Please can you do one where Joe Sugg faints please xx love your writing?

Prompt - Can you do a Jasper one (Joe Sugg centric) where Joe is ill and then he passes out with lots of fluff please x

Prompt - I love your Joe Sugg fics!!!! Did you know how he got sick before Amity Fest? If you did could you write a story going along with that???? I know you’re super busy and I would just be glad if you had the time to write this for me! Thx


——

They had all been very excited for the Amity Fest. Joe, especially, loved these kind of activities. He loved meeting the fans. He adored performing on stage. Basically, Amity Fest was his kind of fan interactions that he liked. But trust his bad luck, Joe happened to fall sick at the Amity Fest itself. The stubborn guy though, tried downplaying it, not wanting to disappoint his fans. But even he knew that it was just going to be a matter of time before his body, literally, cannot hold him up.

——

Joe woke up a day before the functions started feeling very disorientated. There was a dull ache in his bones as well a bit of headache that was threatening to build up. Caspar had doubted that something was wrong as soon he saw Joe’s scrunched up face.

“You okay?” Caspar asked.

Joe nodded, getting up before his knees threatened to buckle down.

“Hey” Caspar shouted as he caught the boy before he could fall down.

“I’m okay. Woke up a little too fast” Joe said as he pushed Caspar’s hands away and walked to the bathroom.

Caspar raised an eyebrow at the boy, deciding to keep a close eye on his best friend.

——

When the boys got down, everyone could see that Joe didn’t look too fine.

“Joe, you don’t look good buddy” Marcus said.

“I’m fine” Joe tried to assure them.

“Buddy, we all can see you are not fine” Tanya said.

“I’m good” Joe said again.

“Joe, do not lie to me” Zoe warned.

“I’m fine mother” Joe snapped.

“Okay… Fine… Fine…” Alfie tried to calm things down.

Zoe shook her head at her little brother, watching the boy be stubborn about his own health.

——

Joe couldn’t stay on his feet for quite long though. His headache had turned into a pounding one and he could feel a cold sweat running down his back.

They were supposed to be on stage in an hour and Joe was stubbornly waiting to be on stage when he started feeling dizzy.

He knew that Caspar was close by but was unable to shout for the man as he started falling forward. But the boy caught him way before he could hit the ground.

“Joe? Joe, buddy?” Jim called out as he patted Joe’s cheeks.

“This kid is too stubborn” Louise sighed.

“Let’s get him back to the room” Tanya suggested.

Zoe share a look with Caspar, both of them sighing as they watched over Joe.

——-

When Joe woke up, he could hear mumbles around him and he could feel something cold over his eyes.

“Let it be” Alfie said when Joe tried to remove the cool cloth from over his eyes.

“I know you have a headache” Zoe mumbled as she ran her fingers through Joe’s head.

The boy groaned as he tried to turn towards Zoe, unconsciously seeking comfort from her big sister.

“What happened?” Joe asked.

“You passed out idiot” Caspar said, before adding, “Oh and you also have a fever.”

“Shit! We need to be on stage” Joe said as he tried to sit up.

“He isn’t being serious” Jim sighed.

“You must be kidding if you think you’ll be allowed to get up from the bed kiddo” Louise warned him.

“But…” Joe trailed off.

“Marcus can replace you for until you feel better” Tanya said.

“We’ll take turn to stay with you” Zoe said.

“I’ll stay with him right now” Caspar suggested.

Hesitating, Zoe still nodded, knowing Caspar will take good care of Joe.

——

As soon as they all left for the show, Joe tried convincing Caspar that he was okay.

“I should have been there right now. The fans would be so disappointed” Joe whispered.

“You can still join them when you feel better but for that you need to rest right now” Caspar emphasized.

Joe sighed as he closed his eyes, hoping the medicines Alfie gave him would kick in soon and alleviate some of the pain.

He let out a sigh of relief when he felt Caspar massaging his temples and tried to ignore Caspar’s chuckle.

Joe didn’t even realize when Caspar left for the stage and Zoe took his place but he did get a hint of his sister’s presence as he snuggled in, trusting his big sister to take care of him just like his best friend had done.

——

A few days later, Joe felt much better to join his group on stage as he gave his fans a sneaky surprise. Throughout it all, he had his sister by his side, his friends watching over him and Caspar, his best friend, always ready to catch him if need be. Joe knew his friends and family would always be there for him and that he was in good hands.

——

A/N

Hope you all like it.

——

They had all been very excited for the Amity Fest. Joe, especially, loved these kind of activities. He loved meeting the fans. He adored performing on stage. Basically, Amity Fest was his kind of fan interactions that he liked. But trust his bad luck, Joe happened to fall sick at the Amity Fest itself. The stubborn guy though, tried downplaying it, not wanting to disappoint his fans. But even he knew that it was just going to be a matter of time before his body, literally, cannot hold him up.

——

Joe woke up a day before the functions started feeling very disorientated. There was a dull ache in his bones as well a bit of headache that was threatening to build up. Caspar had doubted that something was wrong as soon he saw Joe’s scrunched up face.

“You okay?” Caspar asked.

Joe nodded, getting up before his knees threatened to buckle down.

“Hey” Caspar shouted as he caught the boy before he could fall down.

“I’m okay. Woke up a little too fast” Joe said as he pushed Caspar’s hands away and walked to the bathroom.

Caspar raised an eyebrow at the boy, deciding to keep a close eye on his best friend.

——

When the boys got down, everyone could see that Joe didn’t look too fine.

“Joe, you don’t look good buddy” Marcus said.

“I’m fine” Joe tried to assure them.

“Buddy, we all can see you are not fine” Tanya said.

“I’m good” Joe said again.

“Joe, do not lie to me” Zoe warned.

“I’m fine mother” Joe snapped.

“Okay… Fine… Fine…” Alfie tried to calm things down.

Zoe shook her head at her little brother, watching the boy be stubborn about his own health.

——

Joe couldn’t stay on his feet for quite long though. His headache had turned into a pounding one and he could feel a cold sweat running down his back.

They were supposed to be on stage in an hour and Joe was stubbornly waiting to be on stage when he started feeling dizzy.

He knew that Caspar was close by but was unable to shout for the man as he started falling forward. But the boy caught him way before he could hit the ground.

“Joe? Joe, buddy?” Jim called out as he patted Joe’s cheeks.

“This kid is too stubborn” Louise sighed.

“Let’s get him back to the room” Tanya suggested.

Zoe share a look with Caspar, both of them sighing as they watched over Joe.

——-

When Joe woke up, he could hear mumbles around him and he could feel something cold over his eyes.

“Let it be” Alfie said when Joe tried to remove the cool cloth from over his eyes.

“I know you have a headache” Zoe mumbled as she ran her fingers through Joe’s head.

The boy groaned as he tried to turn towards Zoe, unconsciously seeking comfort from her big sister.

“What happened?” Joe asked.

“You passed out idiot” Caspar said, before adding, “Oh and you also have a fever.”

“Shit! We need to be on stage” Joe said as he tried to sit up.

“He isn’t being serious” Jim sighed.

“You must be kidding if you think you’ll be allowed to get up from the bed kiddo” Louise warned him.

“But…” Joe trailed off.

“Marcus can replace you for until you feel better” Tanya said.

“We’ll take turn to stay with you” Zoe said.

“I’ll stay with him right now” Caspar suggested.

Hesitating, Zoe still nodded, knowing Caspar will take good care of Joe.

——

As soon as they all left for the show, Joe tried convincing Caspar that he was okay.

“I should have been there right now. The fans would be so disappointed” Joe whispered.

“You can still join them when you feel better but for that you need to rest right now” Caspar emphasized.

Joe sighed as he closed his eyes, hoping the medicines Alfie gave him would kick in soon and alleviate some of the pain.

He let out a sigh of relief when he felt Caspar massaging his temples and tried to ignore Caspar’s chuckle.

Joe didn’t even realize when Caspar left for the stage and Zoe took his place but he did get a hint of his sister’s presence as he snuggled in, trusting his big sister to take care of him just like his best friend had done.

——

A few days later, Joe felt much better to join his group on stage as he gave his fans a sneaky surprise. Throughout it all, he had his sister by his side, his friends watching over him and Caspar, his best friend, always ready to catch him if need be. Joe knew his friends and family would always be there for him and that he was in good hands.

——

A/N

Hope you all like it.

body:
Wow. It’s been a good bit of 4 months since we’ve posted last! It was a whirlwind for the both of us as 2018 came to an end. There were plenty of changes happening…the main one being that one of us moved from one city to another. It was a stressful time but 2019 was already looking promising and we’re happy to finally let the dust settle! 

What have we been up to since the start of the year? Our biggest mention is our YouTube Channel! As a New Years resolution we decided to act on something that has been in the talks for a while…with the push from our dear friend, Megan, we finally did it. We have yet to miss a week without an upload and are super proud of it. We hope to continually grow as a business. We already know how cringey we will be when we look back at our first episodes haha! 

We’ve already had a handful of photoshoots…from headshots to engagements, but we’re super stoked we already have 5 weddings in our near future! We also just got back from our first trip of the year to New Orleans! We had booked a couple shoots out there and decided to extend the trip and make it something we’d actually enjoy. Our highlights were the airboat tours to see some alligators and getting our dope tattoos! 

In the meantime, stick with us on Instagram as well as YouTube to keep up with our daily lives <3
